Package: TreatTrace
Type: Package
Title: Genotype-Specific Drug Resistance Inference in GIST Using DNA Barcoding
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    c(
      person(given = "Mohammad", family = "Darbalaei", email = "mohammad.darbalaei@uni-due.de", 
             role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person(given = "Daniel", family = "Hoffmann", 
             role = "aut",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2973-7869"))
    )
Maintainer: Mohammad Darbalaei <mohammad.darbalaei@uni-due.de>
Description: TreatTrace enables high-throughput analysis of genotype-specific drug resistance 
    in gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST) using DNA-barcoded cell mixtures. It integrates 
    barcode data with tumor volume or confluency measurements and applies hierarchical Bayesian 
    modeling to quantify treatment responses in vitro and in vivo.
